condition.narrative: All expenditures retained; enabling the Bank's representaties to examine and ensure that all SOEs are included in audit for each FY.
Borrower shall prepare a mid-term report under terms of reference satisfactory to the Bank
Borrower shall prepare annual reports under terms of reference satisfactory to the Bank, and furnish to the Bank, the annual report

Borrower to incorporate appropriate environmental mitigation measures into the design and implementation of school buildings'repairs or constructions in accordance with guidelines satisfactory to the Bank to ensure that this is in accordance with soundenvironmental practices and standards, and (ii) not carry out schoolbuilding repairs requiring land acquisition

Borrower, after furnishing the annual reports will review said report with the Bank and take all measures required to ensure theefficient completion of the Project and the achievement of the objectives based on the conclusions and recommendations of saidreport and the Bank's views on the matter

Borrower, after furnishing the mid-term report will review said report with the Bank, by July 31, 2009, or such later date as theBank shall request, and take all measures required to ensure the efficient compleiton of the Project and the achievement of theobjectives thereof, based on the conclusions and recommendations of the said report and the Bank's views on the matter
Prepare, on the basis of guidelines acceptable to the Bank, a plan for the future operation of the Project
Submission of annual validation reports on school grants due 3 months after the end of each calendar year
The Borrower shall adopt and implement the Project Implementation Plan, acceptable to the Bank and adopt and implement theOperations Manual acceptable to the Bank

The Borrower shall maintain until completion of the Project the Management Committee, Executive Committee, Education DevelopmentProjects Implementing Task Force with DepEd, assigned with such functions, membership, and responsibilities for the Project,satisfactory to the Bank
The Borrower shall; have financial statements audited according to standards acceptable to the Bank.
The Borrower, through DepEd, shall maintain a financial management system, acceptable to the Bank.
The first Financial Monitoring Report shall be furnished to the Bank not later than 45 days after the end of the first calendarquarter after the Effective Date.

Updating of the Procurement Plan in accordance with terms of reference acceptable to the Bank, and furnish such update to the Banknot later than 12 months after the date of the preceding Procurement Plan, for the Bank's approval
Without limitation the Borrower shall prepare and furnish to the Bank a financial monitoring report.
